to the editor if the port authority of new york and new jersey does not scale back its outsized plans for ground zero it will complete the destruction the terrorists began front page july 17 since sept 11 when my neighbors and i had to run from the cedar street lofts we 've called home for more than 20 years we have hauled belongings vacuumed toxic dust endured break ins and thefts and navigated a legal and bureaucratic maze in our effort to return when the environmental protection agency pledged recently to clean our apartments we finally dared hope for a safe homecoming hope turned to distress when it appeared that each of the redevelopment proposals contemplated overriding our vibrant street adjacent to ground zero replacing its existing mix of small historic buildings planners charged with community preservation and renewal should treat our homes as a sort of sacred ground as well mark scherzer new york july 17 2002

